Vice President Joe Biden expresses condolences to the Scalia family on the passing of Supreme Court Justice Antonin Scalia. Biden acknowledges their fundamental disagreements on constitutional interpretation but emphasizes their shared belief in the importance of sharp debates, tough questions, and respect for the adversarial process in the judicial system and democracy. Biden recognizes Scalia as one of the most influential justices, inspiring and challenging generations of students, clerks, lawyers, and judges. He also highlights Scalia's role as a mentor, dear friend, and a man devoted to his faith and family.